The Petre Shotadze Tbilisi Medical Academy, commonly referred to as Tbilisi Medical Academy, is a Georgian private research university located in Tbilisi. The university was founded in 1992 by Petre Shotadze, in whose honor it was posthumously renamed. Tbilisi Medical Academy is the oldest private institution of higher learning in Georgia. The university has a large and distinguished faculty to support its missions of education, research, and clinical care.

